  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Exterior Light Bulb Removal and Installation - Headlight Section"
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "The bulb socket of the discharge headlight generates a high voltage momentarily when the lighting switch is turned on, which is very dangerous, so the bulb must be replaced with the following precautions."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "To prevent electric shock, avoid working in places exposed to rain or water and with wet hands."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Do not touch the glass surface of the bulb with your hands or allow grease or other contaminants to adhere to it.",
        "Bulb replacement should be done when the bulb is completely cool (at least 10 minutes after the light has been turned off)."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Lighting switch OFF"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. 12V battery Negative (-) terminal Disconnect",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000910",
          "label": "12V battery Negative (-) terminal Disconnect",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Valve removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "961_3.0_jpn_11580765_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Remove the cover (A)."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "961_3.0_jpn_11580766_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "2",
      "text": "Rotate the valve socket (A) counterclockwise to remove it. Remove the retaining spring (B). Remove the valve (C). Headlight: 12V-35W"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "4. Installation Precautions"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Installation is the reverse of the removal procedure."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Lighting switch OFF"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Valve removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "961_3.0_jpn_11580767_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Remove the cover (A)."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "961_3.0_jpn_11580768_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "2",
      "text": "Rotate the valve socket (A) counterclockwise to remove it. Remove the retaining spring (B). Remove the low beam valve (C). Headlight: 12V-35W"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "961_3.0_jpn_11580769_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "5",
      "text": "Disconnect the coupler (A). Remove the retaining spring (B). Remove the high beam bulb (C). Headlight: 12V-55W"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Installation Precautions"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Installation is the reverse of the removal procedure."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Lighting switch OFF"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Valve removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "961_3.0_jpn_11580770_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Disconnect the coupler (A). Remove the rubber cover (B)."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "961_3.0_jpn_11580771_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "3",
      "text": "Remove the retaining spring (A). Remove the valve (B). Headlight: 12V-60/55W"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Installation Precautions"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Installation is the reverse of the removal procedure."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Valve removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The front position light is an integral part of the headlight assembly and cannot be detached separately. Therefore, when removing and installing the front position lights, Remove the headlight assembly.",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000964",
          "label": "Remove the headlight assembly.",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Front position lights: LED"
